A temblor rumbled through the Indian state of Assam on the India-China border in August 1950. More than 25000 houses were flattened in Darbhanga, as well as the districts of Munger and Madhubani, Indian officials said. He said 50000 to 60000 houses were destroyed in the Dharan district alone. 5 on the Richter scale. The quake, centered almost on the India-Nepal border, registered 6. Indian officials reported at least 200 people dead and more than 2000 injured, most by debris from collapsing buildings. He said officials expected the numbers to climb. 